            "content": "# Chat List Improvements Design\n\n**Issues**: #175 (TUI Improvements tracking), #169 (ListState fix)\n**Scope**: Conversation list UX overhaul — extraction, rendering, configuration\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nRewrite the conversation list as an extracted `ConversationList` component with proper `ListState` selection, configurable display modes (two-line / compact), trust level indicators, unread badges, relative timestamps, and sort-by-recent-activity.\n\n## Data Model\n\n### Conversation struct\n\n```rust\npub struct Conversation {\n    pub id: i64,\n    pub public_id: PublicID,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub last_message: Option<String>,\n    pub last_message_time: Option<i64>,  // unix timestamp from storage\n    pub unread_count: u32,\n    pub trust_level: TrustLevel,         // Stranger | Known | Verified | Trusted\n}\n```\n\nNew fields: `last_message_time` and `trust_level`. Both are already available from the `Contact` and last-message queries — just not plumbed through to the UI today.\n\n### Sort order\n\nConversations sorted by `last_message_time` descending (most recent first). Contacts with no messages go to the bottom, sorted by `created_at` descending.\n\nRe-sort triggers:\n- `load_contacts()` (initial load)\n- Incoming message (bumps conversation to top)\n- Sent message (bumps current conversation to top)\n\nSelection follows the conversation identity (by `public_id`), not the index. If you're chatting with Alice and Bob messages you, Alice stays selected even though her position shifts.\n\n## ConversationList Component\n\nNew file: `apps/client/src/tui/conversation_list.rs`\n\n### Struct\n\n```rust\npub struct ConversationList {\n    pub conversations: Vec<Conversation>,\n    pub state: ListState,           // ratatui ListState — fixes #169\n    pub display_mode: DisplayMode,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Default, Deserialize, Serialize)]\npub enum DisplayMode {\n    #[default]\n    TwoLine,\n    Compact,\n}\n```\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n- Owns `ListState` — highlight and auto-scroll work via `render_stateful_widget`\n- Navigation: `select_next()`, `select_previous()`, `selected()` → `Option<&Conversation>`\n- Sort: `sort_by_recent()` applies the sort order described above\n- Display mode toggle: `toggle_display_mode()`\n\n### What moves out of App\n\n| From `App`                | To `ConversationList`          |\n|---------------------------|-------------------------------|\n| `conversations: Vec<Conversation>` | `conversations` field  |\n| `selected_conversation: usize`     | `state: ListState`     |\n| Up/down navigation in `handle_key_event_conversations()` | `select_next()` / `select_previous()` |\n\n### What stays in App\n\n- `load_contacts()` — fetches from storage, then calls `conversation_list.set_conversations()`\n- `message_cache`, `contacts_by_id` — serve purposes beyond the list\n- `get_or_create_conversation()` — mutates list via `conversation_list` methods\n\n## Rendering\n\n### Two-line mode (default)\n\n```\n┌ Conversations (3) ────────┐\n│                            │\n│> Alice        ✓  2m  (2) │\n│  Hey, are you coming t... │\n│                            │\n│  Bob          ○  1h       │\n│  Sure, let me check th... │\n│                            │\n│  Charlie      ?           │\n│                            │\n└────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n- **Row 1**: Name (left-aligned). Right-aligned cluster: trust icon, relative time, unread badge.\n- **Row 2**: Last message preview, truncated to fit width, styled `DarkGray`. Omitted if no messages.\n- **Separator**: Blank line between each conversation.\n- **Selection**: `bg(DarkGray)` highlight spanning both lines. `\"> \"` prefix on first line.\n- **Unread**: Bold red `(N)` only when count > 0.\n\n### Compact mode\n\n```\n┌ Conversations (3) ────────┐\n│> Alice       ✓  2m   (2) │\n│  Bob         ○  1h       │\n│  Charlie     ?           │\n└────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n- Single line: name, trust icon, relative time, unread badge.\n- No message preview, no separator lines.\n- Same highlight and symbol behavior.\n\n### Trust level icons\n\n| Level    | Icon | Color    |\n|----------|------|----------|\n| Stranger | `?`  | Yellow   |\n| Known    | `○`  | DarkGray |\n| Verified | `✓`  | Green    |\n| Trusted  | `●`  | Cyan     |\n\nFilled circle for Trusted avoids star/favorite confusion. Cyan differentiates from the green checkmark.\n\n### Relative timestamps\n\nFormat rules:\n- < 1 minute: `now`\n- < 60 minutes: `Nm` (e.g., `2m`)\n- < 24 hours: `Nh` (e.g., `3h`)\n- < 7 days: `Nd` (e.g., `2d`)\n- Otherwise: `Mon DD` (e.g., `Mar 28`)\n\nStyled `DarkGray`.\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Config file\n\nNew `[ui]` section in `config.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[ui]\n# Chat list display mode: \"two_line\" or \"compact\"\nconversation_display = \"two_line\"\n```\n\n### Code\n\nAdd to `AppConfig`:\n\n```rust\n#[serde(default)]\npub ui: UiConfig,\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Deserialize, Serialize, Default)]\npub struct UiConfig {\n    #[serde(default)]\n    pub conversation_display: DisplayMode,\n}\n```\n\n### Runtime toggle\n\n`Alt+L` toggles between compact and two-line during a session (not persisted). The config value sets the initial mode.\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `apps/client/src/tui/conversation_list.rs` | **New** — ConversationList component |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/mod.rs` | Add `pub mod conversation_list;` |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs` | Replace `conversations` + `selected_conversation` with `ConversationList`. Update `load_contacts()` to pass `trust_level` and `last_message_time`. Update key handling to delegate to component. Add sort-on-message logic. |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/ui.rs` | Replace `render_conversations()` with call to `ConversationList` rendering. Use `render_stateful_widget`. |\n| `apps/client/src/config.rs` | Add `UiConfig` struct, `DisplayMode` enum, wire into `AppConfig`. |\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Component trait (#172) — this extraction is a stepping stone, not the full trait system\n- Online/typing indicators — requires protocol-level presence support\n- `ratatui-macros` adoption (#170) — separate issue\n- Popup refactoring (#166, #171) — separate issues\n- Message list improvements (scrollback, selected-message) — separate feature\n",
