            "content": "# Chat List Improvements Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Rewrite the conversation list as an extracted `ConversationList` component with `ListState`, configurable two-line/compact display, trust icons, unread badges, relative timestamps, and sort-by-recent.\n\n**Architecture:** Extract conversation list state and rendering from the monolithic `App` into a standalone `ConversationList` struct in `tui/conversation_list.rs`. Extend the storage query to return timestamps alongside message previews. Add `UiConfig` to `AppConfig` for display mode persistence.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, ratatui (`ListState`, `render_stateful_widget`), serde (config), ember-storage (SQLite)\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| File | Action | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs` | Modify | Add `LastMessagePreview` struct, extend `get_last_message_per_contact` to return it |\n| `crates/ember-core/src/lib.rs` | Modify | Update `get_last_message_per_contact` passthrough type |\n| `apps/client/src/config.rs` | Modify | Add `UiConfig` struct with `DisplayMode`, wire into `AppConfig` |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/conversation_list.rs` | Create | `ConversationList` component: state, navigation, sorting, rendering |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/mod.rs` | Modify | Add `pub mod conversation_list;` |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs` | Modify | Replace `conversations`/`selected_conversation` with `ConversationList`, update all call sites |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/ui.rs` | Modify | Replace `render_conversations()` with delegation to `ConversationList` |\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Extend storage query to return timestamps\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Modify: `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs:1087-1130` (query) and add struct near line 40\n- Modify: `crates/ember-core/src/lib.rs:501-506` (passthrough)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `LastMessagePreview` struct to ember-storage**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, add after the `StoredMessage` struct (around line 53):\n\n```rust\n/// Preview data for the most recent message in a conversation.\n/// Used by the TUI conversation list to show message snippets and timestamps.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct LastMessagePreview {\n    pub body: String,\n    pub created_at: i64,\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update `get_last_message_per_contact` return type and SQL**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, change the method signature and implementation:\n\n```rust\npub fn get_last_message_per_contact(\n    &self,\n    contact_ids: &[i64],\n) -> Result<HashMap<i64, LastMessagePreview>, StorageError> {\n    if contact_ids.is_empty() {\n        return Ok(HashMap::new());\n    }\n\n    let conn = self.conn.lock().map_err(|_| StorageError::LockPoisoned)?;\n    let mut result = HashMap::new();\n\n    // Chunk to stay within SQLite's bound-parameter limit\n    for chunk in contact_ids.chunks(Self::SQLITE_MAX_BOUND_VARIABLES) {\n        let placeholders: Vec<&str> = chunk.iter().map(|_| \"?\").collect();\n        let sql = format!(\n            \"SELECT m.contact_id, m.body, m.created_at\n             FROM messages m\n             INNER JOIN (\n                 SELECT contact_id, MAX(id) AS max_id\n                 FROM messages\n                 WHERE contact_id IN ({})\n                   AND content_type = 'text'\n                   AND body IS NOT NULL\n                 GROUP BY contact_id\n             ) latest ON m.id = latest.max_id\",\n            placeholders.join(\", \")\n        );\n\n        let mut stmt = conn.prepare(&sql)?;\n        let params_iter = rusqlite::params_from_iter(chunk.iter());\n        let rows = stmt.query_map(params_iter, |row| {\n            let cid: i64 = row.get(0)?;\n            let body: String = row.get(1)?;\n            let crea